The pre-sacrifice mechanics in saijah 2 are void.

=====================================================================
I. THE THEOLOGY: HOW HIRCINE LOVES
=====================================================================
Hircine is the god of the Hunt, so he courts what runs. Saijah fled
him -- the refusal with a hesitation in it -- and that made her quarry,
and quarry is the only thing the Hunter values enough to pursue. He
has already slipped her a gift she did not ask for (the "free trial"
senses) and he is circling back.

Ylva was caught years ago. She is his -- body, soul, blood -- and a
hound is loved the way a hound is loved: used, kept, pulled back from
death at Mzinchaleft, and never courted. There is no chase left in
her. Her devotion is precisely what disqualifies her from the favor
she watches fall on an unbeliever. She is beginning to suspect her
god's love has a shape, and her shape is the one that gets the leash.
She cannot even hate Saijah for it, because Saijah does not want it --
which is exactly why Saijah gets it.

AND HIRCINE SEES TRULY. He names each hunter's beast, and he has
named Saijah's. She is not a wolf. The lone wild thing is Ylva's
shape. Saijah hunts WITH a pack she protects, points her kills from
high ground, retrieves what is lost, guards the small and the weak.
Her beast is the HOUND -- and the Hunter considers this the higher
compliment. Wolves are common. A great hound is bred once a century.

=====================================================================
II. THE OFFER: THE ALPHA HOUND (Saijah's THIRD approach)
=====================================================================
APPROACH ORDER (per saijah 2): #1 the white stag in the foothills (done,
the hesitation). #2 the "free trial" senses (done/ongoing). #3 = THIS, the
full weredog offer — the culmination, NOT an early beat.
TIMING: NOT at Ivarstead. At the Bleeding Stair the weredog is only
GLIMPSED — the senses intensify under Hircine's quiet-the-migraine
temptation (see Section IV), but no offer-as-yes/no is made and nothing is
decided. The formal, open offer lands LATER — at the next dragon, or a
chosen moment in the development stretch — and the actual ACCEPT/REFUSE
(with the rebound, Section III) is later still, at the first reckoning
(Gaelen-kill / Razor). Staged, when it comes, as her frustration with
Kynareth's silence peaks. Not words; a demonstration.

THE SHAPE OF THE GIFT: Alpha Lycanthropy in the form that is hers --
a weredog. The original, pure blessing, tailored:
  - She retains full intelligence and personality transformed.
  - A courser's frame built for the partnered hunt: run-down speed,
    leap, grip. Senses that mark and HOLD a quarry once pointed.
  - Pack-gifts where the wolf gets fury: allies she can see fight
    better against the quarry she has marked; the small and weak
    near her are harder to kill. A guardian's blessing, not a
    berserker's.
  - The ceiling rule stands: front-loaded, complete on acceptance,
    the end of her progression. Hircine's gift is a finished thing.
THE COST (unchanged from saijah 2): Nature's Echo silenced by
bloodlust, Kynareth's blessing fading, the joy of the kill where the
world's pain used to be.
GM: spec the full form only if the table approaches acceptance. The
sketch above is the promise Hircine makes; keep it concrete and warm.
He does not manipulate. He offers a hound the only honest thing he
has: a master who answers.

=====================================================================
III. THE REBOUND: SAIJAH'S CHOICE RESOLVES YLVA'S ARC
=====================================================================
Bind both arcs to the single RESOLUTION scene — and that scene is NOT the
Bleeding Stair. It is the first real reckoning: the Gaelen-kill at the
Eldergleam heart, or the Mehrunes' Razor moment, whichever comes first.
That is where Saijah chooses, where the rebound fires, where Ylva's arc
turns. Ivarstead only advances toward it. (Do not stage the rebound until
the Saijah/Ylva relationship has had room to grow — at Ivarstead it is
still raw RIVALRY, Section IV; the bond that makes the rebound hurt comes
over later sessions.)
A god's boon, once shaped and offered, does not evaporate -- a
rejected gift falls to the nearest open hand.

IF SAIJAH ACCEPTS: Ylva watches her god hand an unbeliever everything
  she ever prayed for. The faith breaks. Her arc becomes the open
  door -- power another way, without him. The hound slips the leash.
  (Sheet destination: see Section VI, "The Slipped Leash.")

IF SAIJAH REFUSES: Hircine, with a hunter's economy, turns to the
  faithful wolf standing right there -- and offers HER the blessing.
  As shaped. The Alpha boon is a HOUND'S shape, and Ylva is a wolf.
  Everything she has wanted her whole life arrives as leftovers, in a
  dog's skin. Alpha-hood that reads, to a wolf, as domestication.
  Whether she takes it -- second-chosen, wrong-shaped, real -- is the
  hardest question of her life, asked in front of the woman who
  caused it by saying no.

IF SAIJAH TAKES THE THIRD PATH (neither god): same rebound, sharper.
  Saijah just declared both gods unnecessary. Ylva must decide
  whether accepting what Saijah called a ceiling makes her smaller
  than the woman who walked away.

GM: never script Ylva's answer in prep. Play her honestly in the
moment -- the joy, the want, the insult, the leash -- and let the
table's Saijah choice set the stage. The point of the binding is
that Saijah's player cannot treat refusal as a private virtue. Her
choice has a body count of one friendship either way.

=====================================================================
IV. THE BLEEDING STAIR: WHAT THE PARALLEL EARNS (Fire B beats)
=====================================================================
ALL OF THESE ADVANCE; NONE RESOLVE. No patron chosen, no offer-as-yes/no,
no transformation, no rebound, no artifact crystallization here. Full
corrected Saijah sequence (the double migraine, Kynareth's cryptic reveal
FIRST, then Hircine's quiet-the-migraine temptation) lives in "IVARSTEAD -
the bleeding stair (planning)" Section V; this section is the Saijah/Ylva
parallel layer over it.

THE CHEATED GAME (Ylva vs. the Dagonites). The cultists on the Steps
  cheat TIME -- stolen turns, doubled actions, a hound aged to dust.
  Ylva's doctrine has a name for what she feels: Burning Indignation,
  the Referee's Wrath. She does not experience cosmic horror on the
  mountain; she experiences a rigged game, and she enforces the
  rules. The most theologically serious person on the Stair about
  why the Unmaking is wrong is the werewolf: Gaelen wants to dissolve
  the laws, and Ylva's whole faith is that the laws make the game
  sacred. Give them one exchange. Gaelen is warm, sincere, and
  reasonable -- and Ylva answers him on his own level, in hunt-law.
  Let the table hear both liturgies.

THE SILENCE BREAKS (Saijah and Kynareth). The Throat is Kyne's peak;
  the monastery venerates her breath. The goddess who has answered
  three prayers with the same instruction speaks loudest here -- and
  she does not use words. TRIGGER (per the standing rule: action,
  not prayer): the first time Saijah shows mercy to something
  corrupted on the Steps -- spares it, cleanses it, eases it down --
  the mountain ANSWERS. Wind where no wind should reach. The smell
  of rain through the rot. An updraft under a falling body. Stage
  Hircine's demonstration and Kynareth's answer on the same ascent:
  both voices, maximum volume, one mountain.

THE MASTERS (the monastery door). CORRECTED (June 2026): the Greybeards
  are masters of the Voice and scholars — NOT mages, NOT wizards, with NO
  special senses of any kind. They CANNOT see Hircine's brand on Ylva, the
  stag's attention on Saijah, Ismara in Davinia, or a dragon soul in Bjorn —
  no divine sight, no arcane sight, nothing. (Earlier drafts had them
  "seeing divine claims"; that is void.) What they DO have: they know where
  the Word Walls are for specific shouts a seeker might want — though none of
  THEM can shout. The monastery beat is scholarship and the Way of the Voice,
  not perception of the marked. The Dragonborn question stays a question
  until the party assembles it themselves, much later.

VARON IS ON THE MOUNTAIN (GM ruling -- see Npcs/Varon, Section XVII). He
  follows Saijah up the Stair and WITNESSES the ESCALATION — the god's
  interest, the senses, the rivalry — NOT a resolved choice (the crossroads
  RESOLUTION scene is a LATER beat, not here). The carved hound watches a god
  circle the beast he was surgically forced to become. No lines unless the
  players pull him in. Afterward: the report he must write or falsify -- the
  Colony does not yet know what the Wandering has become.

=====================================================================
V. THE HAWK ARTIFACTS (blank instruments -- new canon)
=====================================================================
The Talon and Feather went through Kynareth's hands in the Midden and
came back changed. Saijah has never used them and no power has ever
been shown. They are BLANK -- divine instruments holding their breath.

They crystallize at the RESOLUTION (the first reckoning — Gaelen-kill /
Razor — NOT at Ivarstead; they stay blank through the Bleeding Stair), by
path:
  KYNARETH: they come ALIVE. The Feather becomes a living updraft
    (mobility, the sudden wind, the soft landing); the Talon roots
    and grows (grasping growth, the purifying grip). Healing and
    sky. Spec on acceptance.
  HIRCINE: they become TROPHIES. The Feather fletches the killing
    arrow; the Talon marks quarry that cannot hide from her. Kill-
    craft. Spec on acceptance.
  NEITHER: they stay exactly as they are -- warm, whole, hers. Tools
    that answer to no god, only to the hand that gave them up and
    got them back. On the third path their silence IS the reward,
    and the GM may let them do small, loyal, unexplained things.
Until the crossroads they do nothing -- but they are WATCHED. Both
gods know what she carries. Neither mentions it first.

=====================================================================
VI. YLVA -- SHEET DESTINATIONS (spec before the session, not after)
=====================================================================
Ylva is a 6 AP Master Hero with her progression complete. Whichever
branch lands, have the result ready so the table moment is not
followed by homework:

THE WRONG-SHAPED CROWN (she takes the rebounded boon): Alpha
  ascension, hound-form. Build as her werewolf statline stepped up
  (controlled at-will shifting, command over lesser were-creatures,
  the pack-gifts of Section II) -- but the form is the courser, the
  guardian, the dog. Her red-and-gold fur stays; the silhouette
  changes. Roleplay load: alpha at last, second-chosen forever, and
  every transformation reminds her what shape the gift came in.

THE SLIPPED LEASH (faith breaks / she refuses): the open door --
  power another way. Build as the mortal-legend track: Legendary
  Hero progression (the Krusp tier), her wolf fading as Hircine's
  claim withdraws -- the 0-HP auto-shift safety net GOES WITH IT.
  She keeps the axe, the doctrine (hers now, not his), and a
  mortality she has never fought with before. The hunter with no
  patron, hunting anyway.

